data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span` of native-sized integers.** Both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` work with `stackalloc`:

```csharp
Span<nint>  a = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> b = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

Tested on .NET 11 preview — builds and runs without issues. The `sizeof(nint)` confirms 8 bytes on this 64-bit system. Note that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context, but the `stackalloc` into a `Span` itself does not.
